title: S.F. Chronicle Top 25: High School Football
text:
Photo: Michael Macor, The Chronicle De La Salle’s Antoine Custer (28) celebrates after his second touchdown in the Spartans’ 52-6 defeat of Long Beach Poly on Friday. Carter finished with 192 yards on 27 carries for De La Salle, The Chronicle’s top-ranked football team. De La Salle’s Antoine Custer (28) celebrates after his second...
This week’s top three teams in The San Francisco Chronicle’s Top 25 high school football rankings remain the same (De La Salle, Clayton Valley and Foothill), but previous No. 4 Riordan dropped four spots to No. 8 after losing 14-6 to Bellarmine, which moved up three spots to No. 7. Also dropping four spots were Monte Vista and Mitty. New to this week’s poll are No. 22 Amador Valley and No. 24 McClymonds, who take the place of no-longer-ranked Dublin and Los Gatos.
